## Is It Production-Ready?

**No.** The codebase is a well-structured scaffold with correct backend wiring, but it fails the "Definition of Done" from the Implementation Plan doc:

> _"The app can create a prompt, create a dataset, run an eval, inspect traces, score outputs, compare versions, and block a release when metrics fail."_

Currently a user **cannot perform any of these actions through the UI**. They can only view pre-seeded/demo data. The backend APIs exist to support all these actions, but the frontend has no client-side interactivity.

