## Proposed Development Sequence

Based on document priorities and dependency ordering, I recommend this execution path:

### Sprint 1 — Make It Interactive (Wire UI → API)
1. Install shadcn/ui components (Dialog, Sheet, Tabs, Form, Table, Select, Toast, etc.)
2. Add client-side forms for: Create Prompt Version, Create Dataset, Add Case, Import CSV
3. Wire Run Builder → `POST /api/runs` with real prompt/dataset/model selection
4. Wire Retry/Cancel/Export buttons
5. Add publish/archive actions on prompts
6. Wire grading review submission

### Sprint 2 — Interactive Detail Pages
1. Add `/runs/[id]` detail page with real-time progress
2. Add interactive trace viewer with collapsible span tree
3. Add comparison report creation form
4. Wire release gate approval flow
5. Add functional global search

### Sprint 3 — Polish & Complete
1. Add loading/error states, skeleton loaders
2. Implement pagination across all lists
3. Fix mobile nav (hamburger → drawer)
4. Add Framer Motion transitions
5. Wire workspace switcher
6. Implement audit log viewer page
7. Expand analytics charts

### Sprint 4 — Production Hardening
1. Add Stripe billing integration (if desired)
2. Add proper error boundaries
3. Add more comprehensive tests
4. Import Google Fonts properly
5. Accessibility audit & fixes
6. Worker resilience (lock expiry, dead letter queue)

